\[(\mu^{G})^{\mathcal{E}^{G}}(A)=\int_{G}\mu(M_{g}^{-1}P_{\mathcal{E}^{G}}^{-1}( A))d\lambda_{G}(g)=\int_{G}\mu(P_{\mathcal{E}^{G}}^{-1}(A))d\lambda_{G}(g)=\mu(P_{ \mathcal{E}^{G}}^{-1}(A))=\mu^{\mathcal{E}^{G}}(A).\]

